parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Suspension Failure (Upper Ball Joint Failure)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the upper ball joint can cause the wheel to separate from the vehicle, leading to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: Loud clunking noises
front end looseness
skittishness
severe vibration
and poor handling felt in the front end section of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vibration and noise can be a sign of a more serious underlying issue, such as upper ball joint failure, which can lead to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: Loud humming noise
clunking noise
and vibration in the front end of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear axle can cause loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: Rear axle broke off
and the vehicle lost control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and failure of brake lines can cause the loss of brake fluid, leading to a loss of braking ability, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake fluid leaks from the vehicle
rust or corrosion on brake lines.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped or failed brake rotors can cause the vehicle to vibrate or pulse when braking, leading to a loss of control and increased stopping distance, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Vibration or pulsing when braking
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake noise or squealing
warping or excessive wear on brake rotors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive brake noise or vibration can be a sign of a more serious underlying problem, such as warped brake rotors or faulty brake pads, which can lead to a loss of braking ability and increase the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Loud squealing or grinding noise when braking
vibration or pulsing when braking
brake pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A failed brake booster can cause the brake pedal to feel hard or difficult to press, leading to a loss of braking ability and increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels hard or difficult to press
brake pedal does not return to its normal position
brake failure or loss of braking ability.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A failed ABS system can cause the vehicle to skid or lose control, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Vehicle skids or loses control when braking
ABS light illuminates on the dashboard
brake failure or loss of braking ability.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Oil Pressure Loss
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of oil pressure and engine stalling can cause accidents, leave the driver stranded, and lead to costly repairs.
symptoms: The engine stalls without warning
the oil pressure gauge drops to zero
the vehicle hesitates or loses power
and the check engine light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission can cause loss of control, accidents, and costly repairs.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle hesitates or loses power
and the transmission shifts hard or erratically.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the radiator and cooling system can cause engine overheating, damage, and costly repairs.
symptoms: The radiator leaks fluid
the engine overheats
and the temperature gauge rises.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: O2 Sensor and Fuel System Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the O2 sensor and fuel system can cause poor engine performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and costly repairs.
symptoms: The engine light illuminates
the vehicle hesitates or loses power
and the fuel system leaks or malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of electrical and accessory systems can cause inconvenience, distraction, and decreased safety.
symptoms: The heater controls malfunction
the radio lights flicker
and the cruise control is inoperative.
